$interpreted: : The day of the duel...
Master Orchid: Chiyuki...
Chiyuki: Don't worry, Master. I'm sure to win.
Mayday: Are you done yet?
Mayday: Don't tell me you're thinking of backing out now?
Chiyuki: I wouldn't dream of it.
Master Orchid: All right... Listen here. Every person here today will be judging you. Whoever receives the most support will be declared the winner, understand?
Mayday: Yes, yes, I know.
Chiyuki: Got it.
Master Orchid: Then let the duel—begin!
Mayday: Take a good look at this!
Wowed Disciple: Hey, what's he doing with those pillars of stone?
Chiyuki: (Those holes all over them...)
Mayday: Hold your horses, I haven't even got started yet.
Mayday: Blood red moon, cover the night with curses—
Mayday: Shuttle into immortality, wrapped in life anew, and break free of your cocoon!
Mayday: [Everlasting Butterflies]!
Wowed Disciple: It's that fragrance again... The same as before, but somehow even stronger—
Wowed Disciple: Hurricanes! Three whole hurricanes racing through our noses!
Chiyuki: So that's what you're up to!
Chiyuki: You're spraying the perfumes out of those holes on the pillars. The added diffusion is heightening everyone's responses.
Mayday: Very observant—Now what are you going to do about it?
Chiyuki: (I don't have anything as special as that... There's only one thing for it!)
Mayday: Showing off your beauty? How common of you.
Master Orchid: Is there something wrong with your eyes, Mayday?
Mayday: What?
Wowed Disciple: It's mangosteen! See how skillfully she's weaving through the sharp mangosteen.
Excited Disciple: Now she looks brave, now elegant—how hard my heart's beating for her! She's gracefulness itself.
Mayday: The Path of Mangosteen... So you taught her this trick after all.
Master Orchid: She learned by her own hard work.
Mayday: I haven't finished yet, though.
Mayday: O benighted sun, rise up through the dark—

Mayday: Marry sword with shield, and forge a new world of chaos—
[Ragnarok Breath]!
Overexcited Disciple: It's the sun! The sun's rising out of the darkness!
Wowed Disciple: A new world is born~ I can feel the vitality pulsing right through me!
Master Orchid: (He's a tenacious one. Just imagine if he could steer his energies onto the virtuous path...)
Chiyuki: (Overflowing with life... That means...!)
Mayday: Ah!
Disbelieving Disciple: There... There's two of her!? And they're different, too.
Wowed Disciple: This one looks like an untouchable ice queen. And that one looks fierce like she's burning up with passion!
Master Orchid: Fire and ice, forging and extinguishing each other. Marvellous, marvellous!
Master Orchid: She's found something to match your Ragnarok Breath.
Mayday: Let's see what the audience has to say about it!
Chiyuki: We've reached a stalemate... We'll have to call it a draw.
Mayday: A draw? Don't be ridiculous!
Chiyuki: Even if we keep at it, it won't be any different in the end.
Mayday: Don't underestimate me. I still have my ace!
Mayday: I didn't plan on using it today. I can't say for sure what's going to happen now.
Chiyuki: Wait! That sounds dangerous!
Mayday: I've made my choice! Witness the limit of beauty!

Mayday: Unearthly blue! Feed your flames upon my will!
Muster the crowds and unlock the unspeakable realm!
Chiyuki: Gyah! The perfume... I... I'm breathing it in...

Mayday: Transcend everything, overturn all!
[Phantom Flowerburst]!
Chiyuki: What the... Everybody...
Chiyuki: Everybody, wake up... Wake up...
Chiyuki: Can't you... hear me...?
Chiyuki: Wait... I haven't... lost yet... I...
Chiyuki: (I feel so relaxed... I just wanna lie down... and stop worrying whether I'm good enough...)
Chiyuki: (And forget about... being Alliance Beauty...)
Chiyuki: ...Alliance... Beauty... Alliance Beauty... Isn't that why I came here... in the first place...
Master Orchid: Here, let your beauty shine through for everybody to see.
Chiyuki: Born from within... the truest and most germinal boundary, a split-second of eternity.
Mayday: What the!?
Master Orchid: Ah! It's...
Master Orchid: It's...!

Chiyuki: Purest snows, unbridled winds,
Bless us with your limitless gifts—
Chiyuki: [Windy Snow]!
Recovered Disciple: Such... pure light... And so warm, too... Is the sunlight caressing me?
Carefree Disciple: It's as if beauty itself is calling my name... I... I can't say it... I can't find the words...
Master Orchid: The limit of beauty... This is the limit of beauty...
Mayday: Don't talk rubbish... You've never seen such a thing! How would you know what the limit of beauty looks like!
Master Orchid: Just look at her, see her simple brilliance. You know it in your heart, too.
Mayday: I...!
Mayday: I... I've lost... I could never hope to touch... the purity of what she's accomplished.
Master Orchid: Mayday...
Master Orchid: And the winner of the duel is—Hanazono Chiyuki!
Excited Disciple: Miss Chiyuki! Congratulations!
Disbelieving Disciple: Who'd have thought you'd master your studies, and triumph in the duel too!
Chiyuki: I've... won? Really?
Master Orchid: Beyond all doubt.
Chiyuki: But how? What did I do?
Master Orchid: You won with your integrity.
Mayday: Miss—no, Master Chiyuki.
Chiyuki: Did you just call me Master?
Mayday: The winner of the duel becomes the Master. Please, Master Chiyuki, let me stay and study under you.
Chiyuki: What... uh... but... Master?
Master Orchid: Hmm~ He admitted defeat, rather than losing outright, so I suppose...
Master Orchid: The rules about leaving forever won't apply this time.
Excited Disciple: Master Chiyuki, we want to study with you too.
Whooping Disciple: Master Chiyuki! Master Chiyuki! Master Chiyuki!
Chiyuki: I'm so happy for all your support, everybody, but...
Master Orchid: This road will take you back down the mountain.
Chiyuki: Thank you for seeing me off, Master.
Master Orchid: Not at all. Will you regret leaving us, though?
Chiyuki: I think I'm better suited to playing a beauty down there than being a Master up here in Infinite Peaks.
Chiyuki: But, Master.
Master Orchid: Hmm?
Chiyuki: I keep worrying about being Alliance Beauty... is that too vulgar of me?
Master Orchid: Everybody has their own path to follow. There isn't just one true way to beauty.
Chiyuki: I'll find something, as long as I keep looking~?
Master Orchid: Hahah~
Chiyuki: Master, I better go.
Master Orchid: Go now.
Chiyuki: ......
